which is exactly the point.

515
00:34:29,058 --> 00:34:32,164
They wouldn't know the network was there
unless they were looking for it.

516
00:34:32,165 --> 00:34:33,465
Further, the network is rerouted

517
00:34:33,466 --> 00:34:35,253
every few days
as a precautionary measure.

518
00:34:35,254 --> 00:34:37,141
If we lose them now,
we won't find them again.

519
00:34:37,142 --> 00:34:38,580
How much time do we have?

520
00:34:38,581 --> 00:34:40,018
12 minutes, 58 seconds.

521
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:41,579
Sidewinder, what's your status?

522
00:34:41,580 --> 00:34:43,639
We're at the dish.
We're cutting through now.

523
00:34:43,640 --> 00:34:47,577
When you open up the panel,
let me know what you're looking at.

524
00:34:47,953 --> 00:34:50,515
I'm looking at a keypad
and an L.C.D. readout.

525
00:34:50,516 --> 00:34:52,532
Okay, um, any access ports?

526
00:34:53,641 --> 00:34:54,641
Affirmative.

527
00:34:54,832 --> 00:34:56,805
Uplink should be coming your way.

528
00:34:56,806 --> 00:34:57,828
Got it.

529
00:34:57,829 --> 00:34:59,974
- Marshall, what are we looking at?
- I'm not sure.

530
00:34:59,975 --> 00:35:02,685
It looks like the network's
not tracking back to just one source.

531
00:35:02,686 --> 00:35:03,682
Meaning?

532
00:35:03,683 --> 00:35:05,325
Meaning when I try to locate the origin,

533
00:35:05,326 --> 00:35:06,732
several addresses keep popping up.

534
00:35:06,733 --> 00:35:09,894
It looks like the information's
being fed by a number...

535
00:35:10,332 --> 00:35:12,144
wait a minute, that is weird.

536
00:35:12,561 --> 00:35:14,363
One of the nodes streams
to Credit Marquis.

537
00:35:14,564 --> 00:35:16,867
- What's that?
- Public front for French intelligence.

538
00:35:16,927 --> 00:35:19,672
That's not all. I mean,
there's a stream to the Russian S.V.R.,

539
00:35:19,673 --> 00:35:21,769
a European pharmaceutical conglomerate,
the C.D.C.,

540
00:35:21,770 --> 00:35:23,270
MI-6, this list goes on.

541
00:35:23,271 --> 00:35:25,006
So they're hijacking government servers?

542
00:35:25,007 --> 00:35:27,212
No, if that were the case,
I'd be able to detect it.

543
00:35:27,213 --> 00:35:28,518
I mean, this suggests...

544
00:35:29,393 --> 00:35:30,643
they are government.

545
00:35:31,708 --> 00:35:32,706
Dad?

546
00:35:32,707 --> 00:35:33,709
Gordon Dean didn't bribe

547
00:35:33,710 --> 00:35:35,797
someone on the inside
to get Sloane out of jail.

548
00:35:35,798 --> 00:35:38,267
His organization
is already on the inside.

549
00:35:38,466 --> 00:35:40,207
Marshall, can you trace those nodes?

550
00:35:40,208 --> 00:35:42,145
Yeah, let me see what I can do.

551
00:35:48,519 --> 00:35:49,519
Right on time.

552
00:35:50,018 --> 00:35:52,330
Network diagnostic is up and running.

553
00:35:54,582 --> 00:35:56,706
You got two minutes to grab that coffee.

554
00:35:56,707 --> 00:35:59,207
Oh, and get me a cup, too? Little cream.

555
00:36:07,508 --> 00:36:08,578
Arvin.

556
00:36:08,579 --> 00:36:10,934
For the next minute and a half,
no one knows I'm here.

557
00:36:10,935 --> 00:36:12,517
Good. Get me out of these.

558
00:36:13,767 --> 00:36:16,142
That isn't exactly what I had in mind.

559
00:36:18,642 --> 00:36:21,082
Okay, I've narrowed the network down
to 12 isolated nodes.

560
00:36:21,083 --> 00:36:23,018
I think I can trace
their point of origin.

561
00:36:23,019 --> 00:36:24,019
- 12?
- Yeah.

562
00:36:24,769 --> 00:36:27,266
"If there was never a one,
there was ever the 12."

563
00:36:27,267 --> 00:36:30,829
In the Caymans, that was one
of Dean's account protocols.

564
00:36:31,156 --> 00:36:32,328
What just happened?

565
00:36:32,329 --> 00:36:35,704
We're locked out.
Let me try to bypass the encryption.

566
00:36:36,319 --> 00:36:37,980
- Oh, no.
- What is it?

567
00:36:37,981 --> 00:36:39,388
"Grade three watchman encryption."

568
00:36:39,389 --> 00:36:41,186
There's no way around this
in six minutes.

569
00:36:41,191 --> 00:36:42,839
The program's requesting an access code.

570
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:43,919
Dean mentioned "watchman."

571
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:46,003
He said when I find the watchman,
he would help me.

572
00:36:46,004 --> 00:36:47,900
This is what he meant.
He has the access code.

573
00:36:47,901 --> 00:36:48,906
Go.

574
00:36:50,473 --> 00:36:51,720
Don't do this, Arvin.

575
00:36:51,721 --> 00:36:54,780
I have the access code.
You can take down Prophet Five.

576
00:36:54,781 --> 00:36:56,017
God forgive me.

577
00:37:02,341 --> 00:37:04,695
Help! Somebody, please!

578
00:37:05,718 --> 00:37:09,280
These walls are soundproof.
There's no point in shouting.

579
00:37:34,718 --> 00:37:38,093
According to medical services,
Dean took his own life.

580
00:37:38,718 --> 00:37:40,569
Apparently with a cyanide pill

581
00:37:40,570 --> 00:37:43,530
he had subdermally implanted
inside his cheek.

582
00:37:44,966 --> 00:37:46,153
I don't understand.

583
00:37:47,090 --> 00:37:48,902
This morning he wanted immunity.

584
00:37:48,903 --> 00:37:50,028
He wanted to live.

585
00:37:51,344 --> 00:37:53,281
Clearly, Dean thrived on power.

586
00:37:53,903 --> 00:37:54,938
Once the drug wore off,

587
00:37:54,939 --> 00:37:57,278
he must've realized
he was facing a life sentence.

588
00:37:57,822 --> 00:37:59,977
Death was easier to accept.

589
00:38:00,154 --> 00:38:03,405
Marshall counted 12 sources
that make up Prophet Five.

590
00:38:03,406 --> 00:38:04,406
12, dad.

591
00:38:05,533 --> 00:38:07,908
It's like the Alliance all over again.

592
00:38:08,091 --> 00:38:09,091
I know.

593
00:38:09,282 --> 00:38:12,091
If they are embedded
inside global government,

594
00:38:12,092 --> 00:38:13,529
where do we even start?

595
00:38:13,904 --> 00:38:15,279
We've already started.

596
00:38:19,902 --> 00:38:21,777
I guess I'll see you tomorrow.

597
00:38:25,403 --> 00:38:27,528
Do you have any plans for tonight?

598
00:38:28,655 --> 00:38:30,280
What did you have in mind?

599
00:38:34,904 --> 00:38:36,779
You're sure you won't join me?

600
00:38:37,157 --> 00:38:38,969
We can drink to your success.

601
00:38:41,031 --> 00:38:42,531
Or perhaps, if you like,

602
00:38:43,907 --> 00:38:45,919
to soothe your guilt.

603
00:38:48,343 --> 00:38:50,780
Guilt isn't one of my driving emotions.

604
00:38:51,093 --> 00:38:52,405
To your success then.

605
00:38:54,344 --> 00:38:57,094
As we agreed,
Dean's operation is now yours.

606
00:38:57,908 --> 00:38:59,283
But with one warning...

607
00:39:00,592 --> 00:39:01,967
I appreciate ambition.

608
00:39:03,593 --> 00:39:06,593
But if you're considering
any further betrayals,

609
00:39:06,842 --> 00:39:09,435
they will come at your own expense.

610
00:39:10,780 --> 00:39:11,780
I understand.

611
00:39:23,781 --> 00:39:24,968
I'll be right back.

612
00:39:34,907 --> 00:39:37,845
A job well done, Mr. Sloane.
I'm so glad you took our offer.

613
00:39:37,846 --> 00:39:40,221
I didn't have much of a choice, did I?

614
00:39:40,532 --> 00:39:42,657
- There's always a choice.
- Yeah.

615
00:39:44,218 --> 00:39:45,218
My daughter...

616
00:39:46,531 --> 00:39:47,968
when will she be cured?

617
00:39:48,343 --> 00:39:50,016
- Soon.
- Soon?

618
00:39:50,781 --> 00:39:52,532
Perhaps you could be
a bit more specific.

619
00:39:52,533 --> 00:39:53,533
I wish I could.

620
00:39:53,969 --> 00:39:56,969
But there are a few more things
we need you to do first.

621
00:39:56,970 --> 00:39:58,997
- We have a deal.
- No.

622
00:39:59,658 --> 00:40:01,075
We have an arrangement,

623
00:40:01,076 --> 00:40:03,970
which you don't seem
to understand very well.

624
00:40:04,407 --> 00:40:05,594
You son of a bitch.

625
00:40:06,218 --> 00:40:07,343
We'll be in touch.

626
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:11,218
Till then,
I want you to remember one thing...

627
00:40:11,907 --> 00:40:15,093
you have something now
that you didn't have this morning.

628
00:40:15,094 --> 00:40:16,681
- What's that?
- Hope.

629
00:40:40,032 --> 00:40:43,343
- Okay, that's the headboard.
- That's the footboard.

630
00:40:43,344 --> 00:40:45,031
That's what I said.

631
00:40:46,784 --> 00:40:49,344
Have you ever actually built
anything before?

632
00:40:49,345 --> 00:40:51,954
Yes, in fact. I built your crib.

633
00:40:52,970 --> 00:40:53,970
Really?

634
00:40:55,280 --> 00:40:57,780
Well, your mother and I did it together.

635
00:41:03,219 --> 00:41:04,219
Done.

636
00:41:04,970 --> 00:41:06,032
Done?

637
00:41:06,969 --> 00:41:08,344
Why? Did you doubt me?

638
00:41:09,345 --> 00:41:10,998
No, of course not.

639
00:41:31,722 --> 00:41:33,534
Get me the screwdriver.

640
